---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const lastUpdated = "2026-05-02";
---
<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy — Notes Automate" description="Privacy policy for Notes Automate: how we collect, use, and protect your information, including cookies, analytics, and advertising disclosures.">
  <article class="legal">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <p>This Privacy Policy describes how <strong>Notes Automate</strong> ("we", "us", or "our"), operating at <code>notes-automate.com</code>, collects, uses, and shares information about you when you visit our website.</p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We collect minimal information necessary to operate the site:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Server logs:</strong> Cloudflare records IP addresses, user agents, and request times for security and abuse prevention. These are retained for up to 7 days.</li>
      <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> We use Cloudflare Web Analytics, which is privacy-first and does not use cookies or fingerprinting. Aggregate page-view counts and referrer domains are recorded.</li>
      <li><strong>Advertising:</strong> We may display advertisements served by Google AdSense. AdSense uses cookies and may collect personal information for personalized ads. You can opt out at <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads">Google Ad Settings</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Affiliate links:</strong> Some outbound product links are affiliate links (Amazon Associates and others). When you click these, the destination site (e.g., Amazon) may set its own cookies. We do not see your purchase details — only whether a referral was attributed to us.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To operate, secure, and improve the website.</li>
      <li>To understand which articles are popular and which need updating.</li>
      <li>To earn affiliate commissions and ad revenue that funds independent reviews.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Cookies</h2>
    <p>We do not set first-party cookies. Third-party services may set cookies as described above (Google AdSense). You can disable cookies in your browser; the site will continue to work normally for reading articles.</p>

    <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Google AdSense:</strong> See <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads">Google's advertising policies</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Cloudflare:</strong> Provides hosting, CDN, and DDoS protection. See <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/">Cloudflare's Privacy Policy</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Your Rights (GDPR / CCPA)</h2>
    <p>If you are in the European Economic Area, the United Kingdom, or California, you have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Request access to personal data we may hold about you.</li>
      <li>Request correction or deletion of your data.</li>
      <li>Object to processing for direct marketing.</li>
      <li>Lodge a complaint with your supervisory authority.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise these rights, email <a href="mailto:hello@notes-automate.com">hello@notes-automate.com</a>. We respond within 30 days.</p>

    <h2>6. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>This site is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect information from children. If you believe a child has provided us information, contact us and we will delete it.</p>

    <h2>7. Data Security</h2>
    <p>The site is served over HTTPS (TLS 1.3). We do not run server-side applications that store user data. Static files are hosted on Cloudflare Pages.</p>

    <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy when laws change or we add new services. The "Last updated" date at the top will reflect the most recent revision. Significant changes will be highlighted in a banner on the homepage for 30 days.</p>

    <h2>9. Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about this policy? Email <a href="mailto:hello@notes-automate.com">hello@notes-automate.com</a> or visit our <a href="/contact/">Contact</a> page.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal { max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2.5rem 1.25rem; line-height: 1.7; color: #1f2937; }
  .legal h1 { font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: .25rem; }
  .legal .meta { color: #6b7280; font-size: .9rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .legal h2 { font-size: 1.25rem; margin: 2rem 0 .75rem; }
  .legal ul { padding-left: 1.25rem; }
  .legal li { margin-bottom: .5rem; }
  .legal a { color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline; }
  .legal code { background: #f3f4f6; padding: 1px 6px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: .9em; }
</style>
